      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 86: Appending /usr/lib/$(HOST)/pkgconfig and /usr/share/pkgconfig to PKG_CONFIG_PATH during contrib builds can accidentally resolve host/system libraries instead of the contrib sysroot, especially in cross-compile builds. That undermines reproducibility and can link incompatible dependencies. Keep contrib pkg-config isolated to $(PREFIX), or gate host paths behind a native-build-only condition.",
