      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 1867: loadMissingBodyOverwrites treats the absence of pluginData[\"bodyOverwrite\"] as both \"not processed yet\" and \"processed but no overwrite was produced\". If a handler intentionally leaves a message unchanged or performs async work, the same message is considered missing on every load/reactivation, causing repeated plugin work and repeated scans. Store an explicit processed marker, or have transformSwarmMessages return/update a state that distinguishes \"no overwrite\" from \"not attempted\".\n```suggestion\n// Example: mark completion even when no overwrite is produced.\nwork.msg-\u003epluginData[\"bodyOverwriteProcessed\"] \u003d \"true\";\n```",
      "revId": "7b2bab5146d2ebaa6f63c19dc5c90a75a88d6fdc",
