      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 271: transformSwarmMessages() invokes every loaded chat handler for every conversation, ignoring the per-conversation allow/deny/toggled state used by publishMessage(). This lets an installed but disabled plugin inspect or rewrite messages for conversations where it is not attached, which is both a privacy and behavior regression. Filter handlers by the {accountId, conversationId} key before calling into plugins.\n```suggestion\nstd::pair\u003cstd::string, std::string\u003e key(accountId, conversationId);\nconst auto toggledIt \u003d chatHandlerToggled_.find(key);\nconst auto allowIt \u003d allowDenyList_.find(key);\nfor (auto\u0026 handler : chatHandlers_) {\n    const auto raw \u003d reinterpret_cast\u003cuintptr_t\u003e(handler.get());\n    const auto name \u003d handler-\u003egetChatHandlerDetails().at(\"name\");\n    const bool toggled \u003d toggledIt !\u003d chatHandlerToggled_.end() \u0026\u0026 toggledIt-\u003esecond.count(raw) !\u003d 0;\n    const bool allowed \u003d allowIt !\u003d allowDenyList_.end()\n        \u0026\u0026 allowIt-\u003esecond.find(name) !\u003d allowIt-\u003esecond.end()\n        \u0026\u0026 allowIt-\u003esecond.at(name);\n    if (toggled || allowed)\n        handler-\u003etransformSwarmMessages(messages, accountId, conversationId);\n}\n```",
